    "created_at": "2017-01-27T00:34:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-27T00:35:48Z",
    "body": "@kevinsawicki yes- we definitely have seen this and other DPI related issues ☹️ \r\n\r\nI have some hints, although I haven't traced it down in the code yet.  The width of the scrollbar is calculated using GetSystemMetrics.  Unless there is a bug in the Chromium code (which is totally possible), I'm thinking that the electron code is processing this in one of the inherited classes (widget delegate, etc).\r\n\r\nThis value needs to be adjusted from DIP to screen size.  It's going to be a similar problem to what I had fixed with the border on 200% with frameless windows:\r\nhttps://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/atom/browser/ui/views/menu_layout.cc#L21-L22"
  },
